<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udovewhispersilk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dove Whispersilk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/21/01 7:10:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToT3 !</span><hr size=1> Dictate has a level cap of 58 (there wont be many 58's in this thing), so its not a problem.  Really charm is only good for enemy pets. The level 59 mez Rapture is pretty powerful, but if your worried about it just have a SK or necro on your team cast AE disease cloud at the start of your fight.  Ill take a 1/tick DoT to be immune to mez anyday.<br>
<br>
Sure casters can run around taping and shadowstepping all day long, but from what Ive found a cleric just standing around and healing (being powered by bard songs) will be able to drive those nukers OOM in the long haul.  You really need a balanced team I believe. healers to combat the nukers, melee to interrupt the other teams healers, and support like bard, druid and enchanter to debuff, dispell and SoW.<br>
<br>
